    <h1>How To Mine</h1>
  </div>

  <h4>You can mine using two different kinds of software as expalined below. Make sure you use the right difficulty to mine as shown on the examples, based on the number of cards you're mining with.</h4><br/>

  <h4>1a.) Claymore Miner</h4>
  <p class="lead">Grab a copy of Claymore miner from <a href="https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=1433925.0" re="nofollow" target="_blank">the BitcoinTalk (BCT) page</a>. The BCT page contains examples of the options you can set for mining.</p>
  <strong>Mining with just 1-2 cards:</strong><br/> <code>EthDcrMiner64.exe -epool stratum+tcp://ethopool.ether1.cloud:1222 -ewal 0x008c26f3a2Ca8bdC11e5891e0278c9436B6F5d1E -eworker Rig1 -epsw x -allcoins 1 -allpools 1 -mode 1 -dcri 1 -tt 60 -fanmax 90</code>.<br/>
  <strong>Mining with a rig of 6-8 cards:</strong><br/> <code>EthDcrMiner64.exe -epool stratum+tcp://ethopool.ether1.cloud:1444 -ewal 0x008c26f3a2Ca8bdC11e5891e0278c9436B6F5d1E -eworker Rig1 -epsw x -allcoins 1 -allpools 1 -mode 1 -dcri 1 -tt 60 -fanmax 90</code>.<br/>
  <strong>Mining with a whole farm or renting hash:</strong><br/> <code>EthDcrMiner64.exe -epool stratum+tcp://ethopool.ether1.cloud:1444 -ewal 0x008c26f3a2Ca8bdC11e5891e0278c9436B6F5d1E -eworker Rig1 -epsw x -allcoins 1 -allpools 1 -mode 1 -dcri 1 -tt 60 -fanmax 90</code>.

  <h4>1b.) Phoenix Miner</h4>
  <p class="lead">Grab a copy of Phoenix miner from <a href="https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=2647654.0" re="nofollow" target="_blank">the BitcoinTalk (BCT) page</a>. The BCT page contains examples of the options you can set for mining. Just edit <code>start_miner.bat</code></p>
  <strong>Mining with just 1-2 cards:</strong><br/> <code>PhoenixMiner.exe -pool ethopool.ether1.cloud:1222 -worker WorkerName -wal 0x008c26f3a2Ca8bdC11e5891e0278c9436B6F5d1E -pass x -retrydelay 2</code>.<br/>
  <strong>Mining with a rig of 6-8 cards:</strong><br/> <code>PhoenixMiner.exe -pool ethopool.ether1.cloud:1444 -worker WorkerName -wal 0x008c26f3a2Ca8bdC11e5891e0278c9436B6F5d1E -pass x -retrydelay 2</code>.<br/>
  <strong>Mining with a whole farm or renting hash:</strong><br/> <code>PhoenixMiner.exe -pool ethopool.ether1.cloud:1999 -worker WorkerName -wal 0x008c26f3a2Ca8bdC11e5891e0278c9436B6F5d1E -pass x -retrydelay 2</code>.<br/>

  <h4>2.) Proxy mining is also available on ports 12222, 14444, and 19999 depending on your preferred difficulty.</h4><br/>

